16 SECTION 5. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 164 IS CREATED TO
17 READ AS FOLLOWS:
18 (1) The president of the Kentucky Community and Technical College System shall
19 employ a chief financial officer who shall be responsible for the development,
20 administration, and oversight of the system-wide operating and capital budgets.
21 (2) The chief financial officer shall provide the president with timely, accurate, and
22 comprehensive financial information, including but not limited to system-wide
23 and college-level:
24 (a) Budget summaries;
25 (b) Revenue and expenditure reports;
26 (c) Fund balances and reserves;
27 (d) Cash flow projections;
Page 14 of 29
XXXX 2/9/2026 11:30 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 113
1 (e) Financial risks, variances, and material changes;
2 (f) Any other financial information that is necessary for informed executive
3 decision-making or requested by the president; and
4 (g) Any other information requested by the president.
5 (3) The chief financial officer shall provide financial information to the board of
6 regents:
7 (a) Quarterly or more often at the request of the president or the board of
8 regents;
9 (b) In a standardized format that allows comparison across colleges and over
10 time; and
11 (c) In writing and in person at a regularly scheduled meeting.
12 (4) The chief financial officer shall certify the accuracy of financial reports provided
13 to the president or the board of regents.
14 (5) The chief financial officer shall immediately disclose any material misstatements,
15 omissions, or financial concerns upon discovery to the president and the board of
16 regents.
17 (6) The chief financial officer shall oversee and ensure cooperation with all required
18 audits and financial reviews of the KCTCS.
