14 Section 9. KRS 164.011 is amended to read as follows:
15 (1) There is hereby created and established a Council on Postsecondary Education in
16 Kentucky as an agency, instrumentality, and political subdivision of the
17 Commonwealth and a public body corporate and politic having all powers, duties,
18 and responsibilities as are provided to it by law, appointed for a term set by law
19 pursuant to Section 23 of the Constitution of Kentucky. The council shall be
20 composed of the commissioner of education, a faculty member, a student member,
21 and thirteen (13) citizen members appointed by the Governor. The citizen members
22 shall be confirmed by the Senate under KRS 11.160, and the commissioner of
23 education shall serve as a nonvoting ex officio member. Citizen council members
24 shall be selected from a list of nominees provided to the Governor under the
25 nominating process set forth in KRS 164.005. If the General Assembly is not in
26 session at the time of the appointment, persons appointed shall serve prior to
27 confirmation, but the Governor shall seek the consent of the Senate at the next
Page 21 of 29
XXXX 2/9/2026 11:30 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 113
1 regular session or at an intervening extraordinary session if the matter is included in
2 the call of the General Assembly.
3 (2) [By no later than thirty (30) days after May 30, 1997, ]The Governor's
4 Postsecondary Education Nominating Committee shall submit nominations to the
5 Governor as set forth in KRS 164.005. On making appointments to the council, the
6 Governor shall ensure broad geographical and political representation; ensure equal
7 representation of the two (2) sexes, inasmuch as possible; ensure no less than
8 proportional representation of the two (2) leading political parties of the
9 Commonwealth based on the state's voter registration and the political affiliation of
10 each appointee as of December 31 of the year preceding the date of his or her
11 appointment; and ensure that appointments reflect the minority racial composition
12 of the Commonwealth based on the total minority racial population using the most
13 recent census or estimate data from the United States Census Bureau. If the
14 determination of proportional minority representation does not result in a whole
15 number of minority members, it shall be rounded up to the next whole number. A
16 particular political affiliation shall not be a prerequisite to appointment to the
17 council generally; however, if any person is appointed to the council that does not
18 represent either of the two (2) leading political parties of the Commonwealth, the
19 proportional representation by political affiliation requirement shall be determined
20 and satisfied based on the total number of members on the council less any
21 members not affiliated with either of the two (2) leading political parties. In filling
22 vacancies to the council, the Governor shall act so as to provide, inasmuch as
23 possible, equal representation of the two (2) sexes by appointing a member of the
24 sex that is the lesser represented at the time of the appointment. If the remaining
25 membership already has an equal number of males and females, the Governor may
26 appoint a member of either sex. No more than two (2) members of the council shall
27 hold an undergraduate degree from any one (1) Kentucky university, and no more
Page 22 of 29
