9 (8) The members of the council shall elect the chair and the vice chair of the council
10 from among the council's membership, and the chair and vice chair shall serve at
11 the pleasure of the council. The vice chair shall serve as chair in the absence of the
12 chair.
13 (9) The council shall meet at least quarterly and at other times upon the call of the chair
14 or a majority of the council.
15 (10) A quorum shall be a majority of the appointive membership of the council.
16 (11) A quorum shall be required to organize and conduct the business of the council,
17 except that an affirmative vote of eight (8) or more appointive members of the
18 entire council shall be required to dismiss from employment the president of the
19 council, and to adopt or amend the state strategic postsecondary education agenda.
20 (12) New appointees to the council shall not serve more than two (2) consecutive terms.
21 (13) New appointees to the council shall complete an orientation and education program
22 set forth in KRS 164.020(24) to be eligible for appointment to a second term.
